                which latter Ages corrupted, adding Prayers for the releaſe of ſouls out of a pretended Purgatory. But this conceit and practice was never known in the Ancient and beſt times: And therfore our honeſt Church reſolving to bring things to their firſt ſtay, threw out of her Prayers this droſs, and litter, and filthy ſtuff, retaining that which was pure and Primitive.
